The U.S. Treasury said it will sell13.2 billion dlrs of three and six-month bills at its regularauction next week.    The April 13 sale, to be evenly divided between the threeand six month issues, will result in a paydown of 12.35 billiondlrs as maturing bills total 25.55 billion dlrs including the9-day cash management bills issued April 7 in the amount of11.01 billion dlrs.    The bills will be issued April 16. Reuter&#3;